<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4970] ClassCastException from getBlob() on string parameter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4970</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you call getBlob() on a string parameter in a CallableStatement, you&apos;ll get a ClassCastException. We should get a proper SQLException.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; java.lang.ClassCastException: java.lang.String cannot be cast to java.sql.Blob&lt;br/&gt;
        at org.apache.derby.impl.jdbc.EmbedCallableStatement.getBlob(EmbedCallableStatement.java:580)&lt;br/&gt;
        at Test.main(Test.java:13)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12495381">DERBY-4970</key>
